                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "interaction",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A harrow doll can cast <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Augury]</em> as part of a harrow reading, which takes the usual 10 minutes.</p>\n<p>When casting <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Locate]</em>, the harrow doll doesn't need to have previously observed a specific object to learn its direction, but instead can detail the direction only vaguely, using such phrases as \"beside a weeping mound\" or \"beneath the lost sky.\"</p>\n<p>When the harrow doll casts <em>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.spells-srd.Item.Mind Reading]</em>, there is no effect if the target critically succeeds its save.</p>\n<p>Each time a harrow doll makes a harrow reading, it also changes which saving throw is affected by its fortune's favor ability.</p>"
