        {
            "_id": "PQCJPgjYoVwBLXyY",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Harrowing Misfortune",
            "sort": 1200000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A creature struck by one of the harrow doll's cards must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:25] save or be cursed with misfortune, which forces the creature to roll twice and take the lower result on its next roll of a specific type, determined by the card's suit (roll [[/r 1d6]]{1d6} to randomly determine the suit). A creature can be cursed with only one effect from harrowing misfortune at a time, with a new curse overriding any previous curse. The curse ends after 1 minute or after the specified roll is made, whichever comes first. The suits and their effects are: Hammers (melee attack roll), Keys (Reflex save), Shields (Fortitude save), Books (skill check), Stars (Will save), and Crowns (spell attack roll).</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Harrowing Misfortune]</p>"
                },
